            "When he returned, he was 58, white-haired, but still roaring. In 1916, at the Lucknow Pact, he united Hindus and Muslims to demand self-rule together. From the stage of a packed Bombay rally, he thundered the words that echo even today: 'Swaraj is my birthright, and I shall have it!' "
